newsitem.title: USA: Complete Management files to list on NYSE.
newsitem.headline: Complete Management files to list on NYSE.

text.p: Complete Management Inc said on Thursday that it had filed an application to list its common stock on the New York Stock Exchange.
The company, which expects to begin trading on or around September 8, said it would adopt the symbol CMI.N.
Two issues of CMI's convertible subordinated debentures will also trade on the NYSE at the same time as the common stock, the company said in a statement.
Complete Management is a physician practice management company operating in New York City, Long Island and the Hudson Valley region of New York State.
